COPYRIGHT NOTE

The program KEZACO is copyrighted ۱ﹼ 1996-97 by Benoit Socias.
All rights reserved.

Personal use of Kezaco is FREE !
But, if Kezaco is used by a COMMERCIAL COMPANY, or by a group of users with enough money, it
has TO BE PAID... I still don't know how much, but a company should understand that an Amiga
Japanese solution is something rare.  I won't ask much, anyway, that's mainly for the principle.
Companies have money... I don't !  So, if they support my work, that's better than nothing.
I you're a company, then contact me at bsocias@ulb.ac.be, or by snail-mail.

Single users MAY send me anything they want, if they ever want... but there is no
"registered" and "unregistered" version, nor keyfile.  I won't force users to send me
money, because I guess many have as few as me... v_v;;

KEZACO isn't yet a SHAREWARE. This program may be freely distributed as long as
   - the executable and documentation remain unchanged and are included
     in the distribution

   - no other charge is made than to cover time and copying costs

   - it isn't spread on Microsoft Network... but who'd be interrested in it there ?



WHY NOT A SHAREWARE

I've spent many hours to build it from scratch...  To reverse engineer the EDict index
structure, to reverse engineer the JIS24 font (that was an easy one...), to reverse
engineer the Verb Inflection table, to build with my few japanese notions an ascii to
kana table (thanks to the old AmigaBasic manual's ASCII table ^_^;;), to discover
Blitz2 little by little, each time a word tokenized... (I'm at last beginning to
read the instruction manual), to make KEZACO "workbench compliant" (huh ?), to type
plenties of japanese texts (which aren't included), ... in one word : to make it work.

So, there's how I'll do it :
I saw that some http/ftp sites asked donations, so that they can buy new hard disks
and so on to give more things to their users...  so, you mustn't send anything, but
if you ever do, it'll be welcome...
Money could be welcome... but you or I would have to change currencies... and I don't
think anybody enjoys this.  I'd be quite happy if you sent me some japanese stuff :
audio tapes, CD (oops... that's quite expensive) or even video tapes (SP or LP PAL, or
SP NTSC or SP SECAM)... but then first contact me, so that you don't send me something
I already have !

KEZACO is freely distributed, and will always be, with all functionality available for
the moment...  There won't be disabled things and so on, 'cos I don't want to send
disks around the world...  But if you ever need to get the last version via mail
(because you haven't InterNet access, or the last shop selling Aminet CDs in your country
just closed, then, that's allright, I'll send you a copy.)

All I ask you for now is to send me a mail telling me that you use it, and with tons
of remarks : how did you succeed in crashing it, what would be nice in next version
and so on..., even if you don't send me anything else... we'll call this 'registration'.

Registrated users with an e-mail address will be subscribed to the KEZACO NEWS mail list,
it'll only send a message every time some new version is available.

bsocias@ulb.ac.be

or

Benoit Socias
11 rue des agaces
B-1430 Quenast
BELGIUM
(EUROPE)

Tel:+32 67 637915


Updates will be sent to AmiNet in the text/util directory.

Shorter updates will be available at :

 http://mach.ulb.ac.be/~bsocias/kezaco.html

"Spread both word and disk !!" - not an Aegis moto

@EndNode

